    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 7000 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - HOOD SEAL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
        <title>HOOD SEAL</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Hood Seal- Removal</title>
            <para>Release the hood latches on each side and raise the hood to the full tilt position. Locate the hood
                seal on the forward edge of the cowl tray (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900748">Figure 48, Item 2</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Beginning on the passenger side of the cowl tray, grip the hood seal and lift in upward
                    direction.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull upward to remove the seal (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900749">Figure 49, Item 1</hotlnk>) from the entire lip of the cowl tray across
                    the front of the cab.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900748" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900748.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 48. Hood Seal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HVAC AIR INLET</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HOOD SEAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. COWL TRAY</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. RADIO ANTENNA</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. WINDSHIELD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Hood Seal- Install</title>
            <para>To install the hood seal, release the hood latches both sides and tilt hood forward.</para>
            <figure id="f0900749" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900749.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 49. Hood Seal Installation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HOOD SEAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. COWL TRAY</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. COWL TRAY FORWARD EDGE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Refer to Figure 49.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place hood seal material on the forward edge of the cowl tray on the passenger side and
                    press down on seal causing the trim lock portion to secure on the cowl tray edge.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Continue across the entire forward edge of the cowl tray with the hood seal material.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check that seal is pushed down on edge as far as is allowable. Lower hood and latch hood
                    release.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
